text:
if you love spicy food, try here! the spicy really kicks and so yummy that feel like you were eating in Indonesia! Aunty Lily is a lovely and wonderful person. Talking to her made you feel like you have a really close fMily member. she is so passionate about her creation and learn cooking Indonesian food since forever!
Believe me, you should try the spice of her food!

Mee Siam is thick and flavourful. Better than Gloryâ€™s IMHO. My wife Nasi Lemak and fried chicken tasted great too. Menu items runs out so may need to come early and get the freshest items. Kueh kueh tastes sweet and savoury.

Brought here by a friend who was raving over Aunty Lily's food. My Nasi Lemak was great, I love the sambal chilli which went so well with the blue pea rice. The chicken was crispy and tasty too.
The Ayam Penyet was delicious, and the Tahu Goreng was very nice. Aunty Lily was very friendly, and even gave us a small bowl of Soto Ayam soup to try. If you're around the area, do drop by. But be prepared to queue as it's a popular stall!

First time here and was initially attracted to the blue pea rice - so many options and also the Tumpeng with Yellow Rice. Ended up ordering the Gado Gado $5.50 gravy was so good, lots of veg and fresh.  Auntie Lily is so friendly. Ordered another Nasi Liwet with Chicken  - so so good also.  We tasted the Belinjo - tasted to good too except anit too sweet for me but we still bought home 2 big tubs (each $18) coz too nice ðŸ˜‚ðŸ˜…. Have to come back to try other dishes and the otah, soto ayamâ€¦.

Auntie Lily is v chill and friendly.
Love the chilli and the nasi, beef rendang are all well spiced! We tried the ondeh ondeh and kueh dadar - both has pretty authentic perenakan flavors too
